   "source": [
    "# Steane Encoding\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the construction and simulation of a logical Steane encoder circuit. Steane code was introduced by Andrew Steane in 1996 \\[1\\]. In surface code, this logical circuit can be used to prepare the magic state for logical S gate \\[2\\]. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Construction\n",
    "\n",
    "`tqec` provides builtin functions `tqec.gallery.steane_encoding` to construct it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<iframe style=\"width: 100%; height: 300px; overflow: hidden; resize: both; border: 1px dashed gray;\" frameBorder=\"0\" srcdoc=\"\n",
       "&lt;!doctype html&gt;\n",
       "&lt;html&gt;\n",
       "\n",
       "&lt;head&gt;\n",
       "  &lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot; /&gt;\n",
       "  &lt;script type=&quot;importmap&quot;&gt;\n",
       "      {\n",
       "        &quot;imports&quot;: {\n",
       "          &quot;three&quot;: &quot;https://unpkg.com/three@0.138.0/build/three.module.js&quot;,\n",
       "          &quot;three-orbitcontrols&quot;: &quot;https://unpkg.com/three@0.138.0/examples/jsm/controls/OrbitControls.js&quot;,\n",
       "          &quot;three-collada-loader&quot;: &quot;https://unpkg.com/three@0.138.0/examples/jsm/loaders/ColladaLoader.js&quot;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      }\n",
       "    &lt;/script&gt;\n",
       "&lt;/head&gt;\n",
       "\n",
       "&lt;body&gt;\n",
       "  &lt;a download=&quot;model.dae&quot; id=&quot;model-download-link&quot; href=&quot;data:text/plain;base64,&quot;&gt;Download 3D\n",
       "    Model as .dae File&lt;/a&gt;\n",
       "  &lt;br /&gt;Mouse Wheel = Zoom. Left Drag = Orbit. Right Drag = Strafe.\n",
       "  &lt;div id=&quot;scene-container&quot; style=&quot;width: calc(100vw - 32px); height: calc(100vh - 64px)&quot;&gt;\n",
       "    JavaScript Blocked?\n",
       "  &lt;/div&gt;\n",
       "\n",
       "  &lt;script type=&quot;module&quot;&gt;\n",
       "    import * as THREE from &quot;three&quot;;\n",
       "    import {OrbitControls} from &quot;three-orbitcontrols&quot;;\n",
       "    import {ColladaLoader} from &quot;three-collada-loader&quot;;\n",
       "\n",
       "    const container = document.getElementById(&quot;scene-container&quot;);\n",
       "    const downloadLink = document.getElementById(&quot;model-download-link&quot;);\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Remove IDs to avoid cross-cell interactions (workaround for Jupyter notebook issue)\n",
       "    container.removeAttribute(&quot;id&quot;);\n",
       "    downloadLink.removeAttribute(&quot;id&quot;);\n",
       "\n",
       "    container.textContent = &quot;Loading viewer...&quot;;\n",
       "\n",
       "    async function init() {\n",
       "      try {\n",
       "        container.textContent = &quot;Loading model...&quot;;\n",
       "\n",
       "        const modelDataUri = downloadLink.href;\n",
       "        const collada = await new ColladaLoader().loadAsync(modelDataUri);\n",
       "\n",
       "        container.textContent = &quot;Loading scene...&quot;;\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Create the scene\n",
       "        const scene = new THREE.Scene();\n",
       "        scene.background = new THREE.Color(&quot;#CBDFC6&quot;);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Set up lights\n",
       "        setupLights(scene);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Prepare and add the model to the scene\n",
       "        processModel(collada.scene);\n",
       "        scene.add(collada.scene);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Set up the camera and controls\n",
       "        const camera = new THREE.PerspectiveCamera(\n",
       "          35,\n",
       "          container.clientWidth / container.clientHeight,\n",
       "          0.1,\n",
       "          100000,\n",
       "        );\n",
       "        const controls = new OrbitControls(camera, container);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Adjust camera to fit the scene\n",
       "        fitCameraToObject(camera, controls, scene);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Add axes helper\n",
       "        const axesHelper = new THREE.AxesHelper(2);\n",
       "        axesHelper.rotation.x = -Math.PI / 2;\n",
       "        scene.add(axesHelper);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Set up renderer\n",
       "        const renderer = new THREE.WebGLRenderer({antialias: true});\n",
       "        setupRenderer(renderer, container, camera, scene);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Start rendering\n",
       "        renderScene(renderer, scene, camera, controls, container);\n",
       "      } catch (ex) {\n",
       "        container.textContent = &quot;Failed to show model. &quot; + ex;\n",
       "        console.error(ex);\n",
       "      }\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    function setupLights(scene) {\n",
       "      const ambientLight = new THREE.AmbientLight(0xffffff, 1.4);\n",
       "      scene.add(ambientLight);\n",
       "\n",
       "      const directionalLight = new THREE.DirectionalLight(0xffffff, 1.0);\n",
       "      directionalLight.position.set(10, 10, 10);\n",
       "      directionalLight.castShadow = true;\n",
       "      scene.add(directionalLight);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    function processModel(modelScene) {\n",
       "      modelScene.traverse((node) =&gt; {\n",
       "        if (node.isMesh) {\n",
       "          node.material.side = THREE.DoubleSide;\n",
       "\n",
       "          if (node.name.endsWith(&quot;correlation_surface&quot;)) {\n",
       "            return;\n",
       "          }\n",
       "          // Add edges for better visibility\n",
       "          const edgesGeometry = new THREE.EdgesGeometry(node.geometry);\n",
       "          const edgesMaterial = new THREE.LineBasicMaterial({\n",
       "            color: 0x000000,\n",
       "          });\n",
       "          const edgeMesh = new THREE.LineSegments(\n",
       "            edgesGeometry,\n",
       "            edgesMaterial,\n",
       "          );\n",
       "          node.add(edgeMesh);\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      });\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    function fitCameraToObject(camera, controls, scene) {\n",
       "      let bounds = new THREE.Box3().setFromObject(scene);\n",
       "      let mid = new THREE.Vector3(\n",
       "        (bounds.min.x + bounds.max.x) * 0.5,\n",
       "        (bounds.min.y + bounds.max.y) * 0.5,\n",
       "        (bounds.min.z + bounds.max.z) * 0.5,\n",
       "      );\n",
       "      let boxPoints = [];\n",
       "      for (let dx of [0, 0.5, 1]) {\n",
       "        for (let dy of [0, 0.5, 1]) {\n",
       "          for (let dz of [0, 0.5, 1]) {\n",
       "            boxPoints.push(\n",
       "              new THREE.Vector3(\n",
       "                bounds.min.x + (bounds.max.x - bounds.min.x) * dx,\n",
       "                bounds.min.y + (bounds.max.y - bounds.min.y) * dy,\n",
       "                bounds.min.z + (bounds.max.z - bounds.min.z) * dz,\n",
       "              ),\n",
       "            );\n",
       "          }\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      }\n",
       "      let isInView = (p) =&gt; {\n",
       "        p = new THREE.Vector3(p.x, p.y, p.z);\n",
       "        p.project(camera);\n",
       "        return Math.abs(p.x) &lt; 1 &amp;&amp; Math.abs(p.y) &lt; 1 &amp;&amp; p.z &gt;= 0 &amp;&amp; p.z &lt; 1;\n",
       "      };\n",
       "      let unit = new THREE.Vector3(0.3, 0.4, 1.8);\n",
       "      unit.normalize();\n",
       "      let setCameraDistance = (d) =&gt; {\n",
       "        controls.target.copy(mid);\n",
       "        camera.position.copy(mid);\n",
       "        camera.position.addScaledVector(unit, d);\n",
       "        controls.update();\n",
       "        return boxPoints.every(isInView);\n",
       "      };\n",
       "\n",
       "      let maxDistance = 1;\n",
       "      for (let k = 0; k &lt; 20; k++) {\n",
       "        if (setCameraDistance(maxDistance)) {\n",
       "          break;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "        maxDistance *= 2;\n",
       "      }\n",
       "      let minDistance = maxDistance;\n",
       "      for (let k = 0; k &lt; 20; k++) {\n",
       "        minDistance /= 2;\n",
       "        if (!setCameraDistance(minDistance)) {\n",
       "          break;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      }\n",
       "      for (let k = 0; k &lt; 20; k++) {\n",
       "        let mid = (minDistance + maxDistance) / 2;\n",
       "        if (setCameraDistance(mid)) {\n",
       "          maxDistance = mid;\n",
       "        } else {\n",
       "          minDistance = mid;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      }\n",
       "      setCameraDistance(maxDistance);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    function setupRenderer(renderer, container, camera, scene) {\n",
       "      container.textContent = &quot;&quot;;\n",
       "      renderer.setSize(container.clientWidth, container.clientHeight);\n",
       "      renderer.setPixelRatio(window.devicePixelRatio);\n",
       "      renderer.physicallyCorrectLights = true;\n",
       "      renderer.toneMapping = THREE.ACESFilmicToneMapping;\n",
       "      renderer.toneMappingExposure = 1.2;\n",
       "      renderer.outputEncoding = THREE.sRGBEncoding;\n",
       "      renderer.setClearColor(0xdedede);\n",
       "      container.appendChild(renderer.domElement);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    function renderScene(renderer, scene, camera, controls, container) {\n",
       "      const render = () =&gt; {\n",
       "        renderer.render(scene, camera);\n",
       "      };\n",
       "\n",
       "      render();\n",
       "\n",
       "      new ResizeObserver(() =&gt; {\n",
       "        const width = container.clientWidth;\n",
       "        const height = container.clientHeight;\n",
       "        camera.aspect = width / height;\n",
       "        camera.updateProjectionMatrix();\n",
       "        renderer.setSize(width, height);\n",
       "        render();\n",
       "      }).observe(container);\n",
       "\n",
       "      controls.addEventListener(&quot;change&quot;, render);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    init();\n",
       "  &lt;/script&gt;\n",
       "&lt;/body&gt;\n",
       "\n",
       "&lt;/html&gt;\n",
       "\"></iframe>"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<tqec.interop.collada.html_viewer._ColladaHTMLViewer at 0x7e175d1b1950>"

    "from tqec.gallery.steane_encoding import steane_encoding\n",
    "\n",
    "graph = steane_encoding()\n",
    "graph.view_as_html()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "We can use the `find_correlation_surfaces()` method to identify all correlation surfaces, and then visualize them using the `view_as_html()` method. In this case, there are a total of seven correlation surfaces. For simplicity, only two are shown here."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "correlation_surfaces = graph.find_correlation_surfaces()\n",
    "len(correlation_surfaces)"
   ]

       "&lt;body&gt;\n",
       "  &lt;a download=&quot;model.dae&quot; id=&quot;model-download-link&quot; href=&quot;data:text/plain;base64,&quot;&gt;Download 3D\n",
       "    Model as .dae File&lt;/a&gt;\n",
       "  &lt;br /&gt;Mouse Wheel = Zoom. Left Drag = Orbit. Right Drag = Strafe.\n",
       "  &lt;div id=&quot;scene-container&quot; style=&quot;width: calc(100vw - 32px); height: calc(100vh - 64px)&quot;&gt;\n",
       "    JavaScript Blocked?\n",
       "  &lt;/div&gt;\n",
       "\n",
       "  &lt;script type=&quot;module&quot;&gt;\n",
       "    import * as THREE from &quot;three&quot;;\n",
       "    import {OrbitControls} from &quot;three-orbitcontrols&quot;;\n",
       "    import {ColladaLoader} from &quot;three-collada-loader&quot;;\n",
       "\n",
       "    const container = document.getElementById(&quot;scene-container&quot;);\n",
       "    const downloadLink = document.getElementById(&quot;model-download-link&quot;);\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Remove IDs to avoid cross-cell interactions (workaround for Jupyter notebook issue)\n",
       "    container.removeAttribute(&quot;id&quot;);\n",
       "    downloadLink.removeAttribute(&quot;id&quot;);\n",
       "\n",
       "    container.textContent = &quot;Loading viewer...&quot;;\n",
       "\n",
       "    async function init() {\n",
       "      try {\n",
       "        container.textContent = &quot;Loading model...&quot;;\n",
       "\n",
       "        const modelDataUri = downloadLink.href;\n",
       "        const collada = await new ColladaLoader().loadAsync(modelDataUri);\n",
       "\n",
       "        container.textContent = &quot;Loading scene...&quot;;\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Create the scene\n",
       "        const scene = new THREE.Scene();\n",
       "        scene.background = new THREE.Color(&quot;#CBDFC6&quot;);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Set up lights\n",
       "        setupLights(scene);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Prepare and add the model to the scene\n",
       "        processModel(collada.scene);\n",
       "        scene.add(collada.scene);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Set up the camera and controls\n",
       "        const camera = new THREE.PerspectiveCamera(\n",
       "          35,\n",
       "          container.clientWidth / container.clientHeight,\n",
       "          0.1,\n",
       "          100000,\n",
       "        );\n",
       "        const controls = new OrbitControls(camera, container);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Adjust camera to fit the scene\n",
       "        fitCameraToObject(camera, controls, scene);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Add axes helper\n",
       "        const axesHelper = new THREE.AxesHelper(2);\n",
       "        axesHelper.rotation.x = -Math.PI / 2;\n",
       "        scene.add(axesHelper);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Set up renderer\n",
       "        const renderer = new THREE.WebGLRenderer({antialias: true});\n",
       "        setupRenderer(renderer, container, camera, scene);\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Start rendering\n",
       "        renderScene(renderer, scene, camera, controls, container);\n",
       "      } catch (ex) {\n",
       "        container.textContent = &quot;Failed to show model. &quot; + ex;\n",
       "        console.error(ex);\n",
       "      }\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    function setupLights(scene) {\n",
       "      const ambientLight = new THREE.AmbientLight(0xffffff, 1.4);\n",
       "      scene.add(ambientLight);\n",
       "\n",
       "      const directionalLight = new THREE.DirectionalLight(0xffffff, 1.0);\n",
       "      directionalLight.position.set(10, 10, 10);\n",
       "      directionalLight.castShadow = true;\n",
       "      scene.add(directionalLight);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    function processModel(modelScene) {\n",
       "      modelScene.traverse((node) =&gt; {\n",
       "        if (node.isMesh) {\n",
       "          node.material.side = THREE.DoubleSide;\n",
       "\n",
       "          if (node.name.endsWith(&quot;correlation_surface&quot;)) {\n",
       "            return;\n",
       "          }\n",
       "          // Add edges for better visibility\n",
       "          const edgesGeometry = new THREE.EdgesGeometry(node.geometry);\n",
       "          const edgesMaterial = new THREE.LineBasicMaterial({\n",
       "            color: 0x000000,\n",
       "          });\n",
       "          const edgeMesh = new THREE.LineSegments(\n",
       "            edgesGeometry,\n",
       "            edgesMaterial,\n",
       "          );\n",
       "          node.add(edgeMesh);\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      });\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    function fitCameraToObject(camera, controls, scene) {\n",
       "      let bounds = new THREE.Box3().setFromObject(scene);\n",
       "      let mid = new THREE.Vector3(\n",
       "        (bounds.min.x + bounds.max.x) * 0.5,\n",
       "        (bounds.min.y + bounds.max.y) * 0.5,\n",
       "        (bounds.min.z + bounds.max.z) * 0.5,\n",
       "      );\n",
       "      let boxPoints = [];\n",
       "      for (let dx of [0, 0.5, 1]) {\n",
       "        for (let dy of [0, 0.5, 1]) {\n",
       "          for (let dz of [0, 0.5, 1]) {\n",
       "            boxPoints.push(\n",
       "              new THREE.Vector3(\n",
       "                bounds.min.x + (bounds.max.x - bounds.min.x) * dx,\n",
       "                bounds.min.y + (bounds.max.y - bounds.min.y) * dy,\n",
       "                bounds.min.z + (bounds.max.z - bounds.min.z) * dz,\n",
       "              ),\n",
       "            );\n",
       "          }\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      }\n",
       "      let isInView = (p) =&gt; {\n",
       "        p = new THREE.Vector3(p.x, p.y, p.z);\n",
       "        p.project(camera);\n",
       "        return Math.abs(p.x) &lt; 1 &amp;&amp; Math.abs(p.y) &lt; 1 &amp;&amp; p.z &gt;= 0 &amp;&amp; p.z &lt; 1;\n",
       "      };\n",
       "      let unit = new THREE.Vector3(0.3, 0.4, 1.8);\n",
       "      unit.normalize();\n",
       "      let setCameraDistance = (d) =&gt; {\n",
       "        controls.target.copy(mid);\n",
       "        camera.position.copy(mid);\n",
       "        camera.position.addScaledVector(unit, d);\n",
       "        controls.update();\n",
       "        return boxPoints.every(isInView);\n",
       "      };\n",
       "\n",
       "      let maxDistance = 1;\n",
       "      for (let k = 0; k &lt; 20; k++) {\n",
       "        if (setCameraDistance(maxDistance)) {\n",
       "          break;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "        maxDistance *= 2;\n",
       "      }\n",
       "      let minDistance = maxDistance;\n",
       "      for (let k = 0; k &lt; 20; k++) {\n",
       "        minDistance /= 2;\n",
       "        if (!setCameraDistance(minDistance)) {\n",
       "          break;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      }\n",
       "      for (let k = 0; k &lt; 20; k++) {\n",
       "        let mid = (minDistance + maxDistance) / 2;\n",
       "        if (setCameraDistance(mid)) {\n",
       "          maxDistance = mid;\n",
       "        } else {\n",
       "          minDistance = mid;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      }\n",
       "      setCameraDistance(maxDistance);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    function setupRenderer(renderer, container, camera, scene) {\n",
       "      container.textContent = &quot;&quot;;\n",
       "      renderer.setSize(container.clientWidth, container.clientHeight);\n",
       "      renderer.setPixelRatio(window.devicePixelRatio);\n",
       "      renderer.physicallyCorrectLights = true;\n",
       "      renderer.toneMapping = THREE.ACESFilmicToneMapping;\n",
       "      renderer.toneMappingExposure = 1.2;\n",
       "      renderer.outputEncoding = THREE.sRGBEncoding;\n",
       "      renderer.setClearColor(0xdedede);\n",
       "      container.appendChild(renderer.domElement);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    function renderScene(renderer, scene, camera, controls, container) {\n",
       "      const render = () =&gt; {\n",
       "        renderer.render(scene, camera);\n",
       "      };\n",
       "\n",
       "      render();\n",
       "\n",
       "      new ResizeObserver(() =&gt; {\n",
       "        const width = container.clientWidth;\n",
       "        const height = container.clientHeight;\n",
       "        camera.aspect = width / height;\n",
       "        camera.updateProjectionMatrix();\n",
       "        renderer.setSize(width, height);\n",
       "        render();\n",
       "      }).observe(container);\n",
       "\n",
       "      controls.addEventListener(&quot;change&quot;, render);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    init();\n",
       "  &lt;/script&gt;\n",
       "&lt;/body&gt;\n",
       "\n",
       "&lt;/html&gt;\n",
       "\"></iframe>"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<tqec.interop.collada.html_viewer._ColladaHTMLViewer at 0x7e175fb49d10>"
      ]

    "from tqec import compile_block_graph, NoiseModel, Basis\n",
    "\n",
    "graph = steane_encoding(Basis.X)\n",
    "compiled_graph = compile_block_graph(graph)\n",

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "## Simulation\n",
    "\n",
    "Here we show the simulation results for all the seven observables under uniform depolarizing noise model.\n",
    "\n",
    "<details> <summary> Click to show the full code used for simulation </summary>\n",
    "\n",
    "```py\n",
    "\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy\n",
    "import sinter\n",
    "\n",
    "from tqec.gallery import steane_encoding\n",
    "from tqec import NoiseModel\n",
    "from tqec.simulation.plotting.inset import plot_observable_as_inset\n",
    "from tqec.simulation.simulation import start_simulation_using_sinter\n",
    "from tqec.utils.enums import Basis\n",
    "\n",
    "SAVE_DIR = Path(\"results\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def generate_graphs(support_observable_basis: Basis) -> None:\n",
    "    block_graph = steane_encoding(support_observable_basis)\n",
    "    zx_graph = block_graph.to_zx_graph()\n",
    "\n",
    "    correlation_surfaces = block_graph.find_correlation_surfaces()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Start simulation using sinter, note that the `save_resume_filepath` is useful\n",
    "    # when simulation takes a long time.\n",
    "    # If the Python interpreter is stopped or killed, calling this method again with\n",
    "    # the same file path will load the previous results and resume from where it left off.\n",
    "    stats = start_simulation_using_sinter(\n",
    "        block_graph,\n",
    "        range(1, 4),\n",
    "        list(numpy.logspace(-4, -1, 10)),\n",
    "        NoiseModel.uniform_depolarizing,\n",
    "        manhattan_radius=2,\n",
    "        observables=correlation_surfaces,\n",
    "        num_workers=20,\n",
    "        max_shots=10_000_000,\n",
    "        max_errors=5_000,\n",
    "        decoders=[\"pymatching\"],\n",
    "        print_progress=True,\n",
    "        # save_resume_filepath=SAVE_DIR / \"steane_encoding_sim.txt\",\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    for i, stat in enumerate(stats):\n",
    "        fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "        sinter.plot_error_rate(\n",
    "            ax=ax,\n",
    "            stats=stat,\n",
    "            x_func=lambda stat: stat.json_metadata[\"p\"],\n",
    "            failure_units_per_shot_func=lambda stat: stat.json_metadata[\"d\"],\n",
    "            group_func=lambda stat: stat.json_metadata[\"d\"],\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        plot_observable_as_inset(ax, zx_graph, correlation_surfaces[i])\n",
    "        ax.grid(axis=\"both\")\n",
    "        ax.legend()\n",
    "        ax.loglog()\n",
    "        ax.set_title(\"Steane Encoding Error Rate\")\n",
    "        ax.set_xlabel(\"Physical Error Rate\")\n",
    "        ax.set_ylabel(\"Logical Error Rate(per round)\")\n",
    "        fig.savefig(\n",
    "            SAVE_DIR\n",
    "            / f\"steane_encoding_result_{support_observable_basis}_observable_{i}.png\"\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def main():\n",
    "    SAVE_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "    generate_graphs(Basis.X)\n",
    "    generate_graphs(Basis.Z)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
    "    main()\n",
    "```\n",
